&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Please note you may be required to work at any site or within any Directorate/Department within the Trust if necessary to meet service needs)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a full time Band 6 Research Nurse to join the Stroke Research Team delivering a varied portfolio of academic and commercially sponsored research studies ranging from experimental treatments, given within minutes/hours of stroke, to secondary prevention&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a clinical patient facing post, which requires a dynamic individual who can work both individually and as part of a team. The successful applicant will be expected to work with the clinical team delivering 7 day research and clinical care. They will be required to manage their own caseload of patients in a variety of clinical trials as well as taking on leadership aspects as part of their professional development within the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please refer to the Job Description and Person Specification for all essential and desirable criteria required for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to arrange an informal visit please don’t hesitate to contact John Davis 0191 28 21688.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
